content: Took the state written test for DO Utility in 2021 in colorado on the first 4 Chapters. I was taking the practice exams on all 4 chapters that is a little over 200 questions. I was consistently scoring 97% only missing 4-6 total questions on the practice exams. I ended up failing my DO test with a 68% I would try something else.
Not compatible with newer versions of Android
Awesome and helpful. I will get the hazmat tech one and fire officer II one when I test for them! This and the instructor were very helpful!

The app has been very helpful for quizzing myself and studying. I'd like to see an option to select between metric and customary units. The metric questions have thrown off the results and tracking improvement.

Good app to study from. Lots of questions similar to the test. The test had many questions on hydrant colors and classifications. There is nothing like this on the study guide or text book. I had to look it up on ifsta essentials. Also there were multiple questions on stand pipes. I found a few of the questions on here helpful.
This app is nice and gives you the material you need to know. I do feel like it should be updated with the newest edition of IFSTA.
Great for a studyguide on the go. Keeps ya sharp although ive heard none the questions on this app are question actual teat bank questions, but i still like the app a lot.
Worthless app. 75 questions on my exam and only 3 were similar to this study guide. Don't waste your money.
Useless app. The questions were not similar in any way to the real test. Absolute waste of time and money.

Would give 5 stars if it had a second prompt for exiting an exam. It's too easy to accidentally close an exam you're in the middle of. It would be nice if after the exit button were pushed there was a second window to ask you if you really wanted to exit the exam.
